1S Pass 1NT Pass 2C Pass 2S Pass Pass Pass
{South opens 1\S.  
With 9 points and a doubleton \S you must respond 1NT.   Partner rebids 2\c.   

North prefers \C over \S but must allow for the possibility that South has bid a 3-card suit. So North gives a preference to 2\S. This is called a "false preference", but it assures the team of being in at least a 7-card fit. 
South happily passes and the pair lands in a reasonable contract, probably better than 1NT.}

